# __caret train function__
## __train__
This function takes a <br />
formula __or__ dataframe <br />
partitioned data set <br />
A method (in this case we use naive bayes: "naive_bayes", LDA: "lda", QDA: "qda", logistic regression: "glm"(binary class) or "glmnet"(multi class) <br />
preProc - signifies how data was preproccessed (center, scale, imputation techniques, feature selection, dim reduction) <br />
trControl - signify resampling methods (bagging, boosting, k-fold cross)<br />
tuneLength - controls size of tune grid<br />
tuneGrid - dataframe of hyperparameters with values<br />

## __predict__

This function takes a <br />
model - this is the model that we trained with the train function. <br />
data - this is the other part of the data that was split initially.

## __coeff__ __&__ __print__

coef - will get the coeff of the model made with the train function for glm models. <br />
print - the print function will return train function info to the console.


## __using these__

* obtain data set.

* train data with train function (selecting the correct algorithm).
* use predict to test model on the test data.
* use print and coeff functions to obtain the coefficeants of the model.
